      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the vegetables for the base</strong></p>\r\n<p>Discard some of the oil from the <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> so you're left with just 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span>.&nbsp;Return&nbsp;the <strong>dish</strong> to a medium heat.</p>\r\n<p>Once hot,&nbsp;add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>carrot</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>rosemary</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 minutes or until starting to soften.</p>\r\n<p>Once softened, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>beef stock</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 3-4 minutes.</p>",
